added.title: Legendary Sandwich
added.description: The team goes on a series of epic quests in order to create the world's perfect sandwich.

added.title: The Mystery of Haunted Island
added.description: The Harlem Globetrotters and Scooby and his friends are hijacked to a haunted island for an experience they will never forget. Taking refuge in an old mansion, they witness statues moving, leaving behind luminous footprints and handprints! Following the clues, the kids eventually emerge from the haunted house and discover the truth.

added.title: The Haunted Showboat
added.description: Scooby-Doo and the gang, along with the rock group Josie and the Pussycats, battle ghosts haunting the Dixie Queen Showboat on the Missouri River. The mystery begins when the 100-year-old ghost of Injun Joe, a Mark Twain character from Tom Sawyer, along with another ghost, drag chains, move objects and make scary noises.

added.title: Scooby-Doo Meets Jeannie
added.description: On a trip back in time, Scooby and the gang meet a genie, Jeannie, as they travel to Persia to help a prince fight evil ghosts. They learn of a legend many thousands of years ago of an ancestor of the prince imprisoned an evil Jinn in a bottle. Now, with the assistance of the prince's greedy uncle, the vengeful genie initiates a sinister plan to scare the prince into abandoning the palace.

added.title: The Spirited Spooked Sports Show
added.description: Tim Conway, a coach at Velma's alma mater, enlists Scooby and the gang to eliminate ghosts haunting the debt-ridden school. The only opportunity to raise money for the school, the All Sports Benefit Show, has been postponed because no teams will play in the haunted high school and people refuse to attend any event held there.

added.title: The Exterminator
added.description: Scooby and the gang stop on Sunset Boulevard to help troubled motorist Don Adams. But the engine is infested with some vengeful, metal-munching termites that completely devour the motor. Scooby and the gang volunteer to help Adams with his next exterminator job.

added.title: Weird Winds of Winona
added.description: After the Mystery Machine breaks down in Winona, Mississippi, Scooby and the gang join forces with Speed Buggy and his buddies to quell the mysterious midnight winds that spook the inhabitants of the tiny village.

added.title: The Haunted Candy Factory
added.description: Cass Elliot, former singer with The Mamas and the Papas, hires Scooby-Doo and the Mystery, Inc. kids to investigate two living globs of green cotton candy creating a sticky mess at her Sugarplum Candy Company.

added.title: Scooby-Doo Meets Dick Van Dyke
added.description: Dick Van Dyke purchases a carnival and names it the Dick Van Dyke Barrel of Fun. But the place isn't fun. It's haunted! Scooby and the gang, who take a night off from chasing spooks to visit the carnival, help Dick uncover the apparitions that are scaring away both customers and employees.

added.title: Come Undone
added.description: It's the end of the world! And our heroes must work together to ultimately realize their love for each other is the true Heart of the Jaguar.

added.title: Through the Curtain
added.description: Traveling through the underground caverns, our heroes trail Pericles and company.

added.title: Gates of Gloom
added.description: Professor Pericles and what's left of his Mystery Incorporated are looking for the entrance into the caverns, where the cursed treasure and the Evil Entity are buried.

added.title: Dark Night of the Hunters
added.description: Searching for the Heart of the Jaguar, the Mystery Incorporated gang heads down south of the border.

added.title: Nightmare in Red
added.description: Our heroes allow themselves to be hypnotized so that they can enter the dreamworld.

added.title: The Man in the Mirror
added.description: In the basement of a local haunted mansion, the gang finds a strange mirror with a mind of its own.

added.title: Stand and Deliver
added.description: A dandy, well-groomed, 18th century Englishman haunts the highways of Crystal Cove.

added.title: The Devouring
added.description: A famous band, whose members died 30 years ago in a plane crash in Crystal Cove, comes back to haunt the town on the 30th anniversary of their death.

added.title: Dance of the Undead
added.description: When Crystal Cove's favorite southern celebrity chef has a cooking accident, strange incidents ensue.

added.title: The Horrible Herd
added.description: A heard of supernatural skull cattle wreak havoc on Crystal Cove.

added.title: Aliens Among Us
added.description: The gang investigates some potential extra-terrestrial life in Crystal Cove with the help of Velma's mother.

added.title: Theater of Doom
added.description: Life imitates art in Crystal Cove's annual Haunted Historical Pageant.

added.title: Heart of Evil
added.description: Dr. Zin, of Jonny Quest fame, wreaks havoc on Crystal Cove.

added.title: Wrath of the Krampus
added.description: When the strange appearance of a mean goat-man demon named Krampus terrorizes naughty kids all over town, the Mystery Inc. gang decide to look into things. Chasing Krampus all over Crystal Cove, they try to second-guess the crazy, evil goat-man's motives and who could be behind the mystery.

added.title: Scarebear
added.description: The mayor of Crystal Cove has his camping trip ruined by the evil Scarebear and the gang is on the case.

added.title: The Midnight Zone
added.description: When the DJ at the local radio station, K-GHOUL, is attacked, the gang investigates.

added.title: Night Terrors
added.description: When a visiting family finds some terrifying specters in an old library high in the hills above Crystal Cove, the gang investigates.

added.title: Grim Judgement
added.description: Hebediah Grim, a menacing Puritannical ancestor of Crystal Cove, terrorizes Lovers Lane.

added.title: Night on Haunted Mountain
added.description: When Ethan and Gary are mountain climbing Mount Diabla out in the desert, they're attacked by Lilith, a dark-winged angel of destruction.

added.title: The Gathering Gloom
added.description: When the gang is at Crystal Cove Cemetery watching a free screening of an old Vincent Van Ghoul movie with half the town, they are attacked by the Graveyard Ghoul!

added.title: Art of Darkness!
added.description: World-renowned modern artist Randy Warsaw is Crystal Cove's greatest art treasure. But when Warsaw's greatest work of art, Junk, comes to life and tries to destroy Warsaw, Mayor Nettles asks the gang to investigate.

added.title: The Hodag of Horror
added.description: A traveling curio wagon arrives in Crystal Cove and a carnie-barker by the name of Gene Shepherd unveils the Hodag, a beast supposed to be found in the wilds of Wisconsin. It's a horrible fake. But when it comes to life and starts stealing, the gang investigates.

added.title: Web of the Dreamweaver
added.description: A rash of strange crimes happen when a number of prominent Crystal Cove citizens destroy the things they love most - a car, a house, a food empire. The gang investigates and soon discovers each of these citizens had a dream wherein the Dreamweaver, a horrible goblin-king, told them to do it.

added.title: The Night the Clown Cried II: Tears of Doom
added.description: Crybaby Clown is back with a vengeance. He's kidnapping all sorts of folks all over Crystal Cove - namely a therapist, a hairdresser, a plastic surgeon and a publicist!

added.title: House of the Nightmare Witch
added.description: A Russian museum exhibit comes to life. It's an evil Russian witch by the name of Baba Yaga. The gang hunts Baba Yaga in Crystal Cove's Haunted Forest of Doom only to end up being the hunted.

added.title: The Night the Clown Cried
added.description: With the gang split up, Crystal Cove is being tormented by an evil-man-baby called Crybaby Clown!

added.title: Ghastly Ghost Town
added.description: After a king-sized bat forces the Mystery Machine into a sandpit, Scooby and the gang cross the desert on foot seeking help. Soon, they meet the Three Stooges, who are actually the ones in need of help!

added.title: Scooby-Doo Meets the Addams Family
added.description: Scooby and the gang consent to spend the weekend as housekeepers in the spooky home of the Addams Family so Morticia and Gomez Addams can take a much needed vacation in Okeefenokee swamp.

added.title: The Frickert Fracas
added.description: When Jonathan Winters invites Scooby and the gang to stay at the farm of his friend, Maude Frickert, they mistakenly believe it will be a vacation from haunted houses and spooky characters. They soon learn differently when vandalizing scoundrels and truly scary scarecrows overrun Maude's farm.

added.title: Guess Who's Knott Coming to Dinner
added.description: When the hopelessly lost members of Mystery, Inc. enter Moody Manor to ask for directions, Don Knotts, the world's greatest detective, mistakenly believes they are the relatives of the estate's wealthy late owner. Don suspects one of them murdered Captain Moody!

added.title: A Good Medium Is Rare
added.description: The gang finds a dog with a diamond collar. They return the dog to the owner, Phyllis Diller, who lives in an old, creepy house. Scooby and friends tour the home and discover it is apparently haunted by Phyllis' ex-husbands. Scooby unravels the mystery of these strange occurrences.

added.title: The Secret of Shark Island
added.description: Scooby-Doo and the gang give singers Sonny and Cher a ride after their car breaks down in a fierce storm. The kids take the two performers to the rambling, run-down Hideaway Hotel, an off-season beach retreat, where they have planned a delayed honeymoon away from the crowds. But soon, strange happenings interrupt the couple's happiness, and Scooby and the gang investigate.

added.title: The Spooky Fog
added.description: A unique form of small-town hospitality awaits Scooby and the gang. Police officer Don Knotts invites them to spend the night in the finest accommodations in Juneberry, the local jail! But soon, the kids help Don solve the mystery of the spooky fog.

added.title: Scooby-Doo Meets Laurel and Hardy
added.description: Scooby and the gang join wits with Laurel and Hardy, newly appointed bellhops at a Vermont ski lodge, to track an abominable snowman by the name of Bigfoot!

added.title: Ghost of the Red Baron
added.description: The members of Mystery, Inc. join with the Three Stooges to thwart the ghost of the Red Baron, a daring evildoer who has scared away all of farmer Sawyer's crop-dusting pilots in an effort to pressure Sawyer into leaving his land.

added.title: The Ghostly Creep from the Deep
added.description: The members of Mystery, Inc. join forces with the Harlem Globetrotters on the eerie banks of a haunted swamp to battle supernatural spirits unleashed by the ghost of Redbeard the pirate!

added.title: The Haunted Horseman in Hagglethorn Hall
added.description: The gang must prove a ghostly horseman haunting Hagglethorn Castle is a fake apparition. Otherwise, Davy Jones' uncle will have to sell the Scottish fortress, once a thriving tourist spot, to the greedy Duke of Strathmore.

added.title: The Phantom of the Country Music Hall
added.description: An exciting evening at the Grand Old Opry in Nashville proves to be almost too exciting when a mysterious phantom appears. It's a haunting experience for the members of Mystery, Inc. when they must search for their missing friend, country singer Jerry Reed.

added.title: The Caped Crusader Caper
added.description: Scooby and Mystery Inc. meet the terrible twosome, Penguin and Joker, on a camping trip in the forest. To stop the evildoers, the kids enlist the aid of those crusaders against crime, Batman and Robin. Penguin and Joker plan to steal the newest invention of Professor Flakey, a flying suit but Scooby and Shaggy's bumbling antics foil the criminals' scheme.

added.title: The Lochness Mess
added.description: When Scooby-Doo and the kids travel to a small New England town to visit Shaggy's Uncle Nathaniel, they plunge into a maelstrom of mystery, encounter the ghost of Paul Revere and confront a spooky sea serpent! With the aid of the Harlem Globetrotters, who are vacationing nearby, the kids discover the actual culprit.

removed.title: Never Ape an Ape Man
removed.description: The gang is hired by Daphne's uncle, a famous director, as extras in his latest project. But the star of the show is a real nasty ape.

removed.title: Battle of the Humungonauts
removed.description: A pair of brutal gargantuas begin breaking apart the town, which sadly mirrors the fractured relationship of Mystery Inc. See, while searching for Shaggy, Scooby accidentally discovers him canoodling with Velma. Feeling betrayed, Scooby is inconsolable despite the best efforts of Fred and Daphne to cheer him up and put the team back together. Although they ultimately reunite to capture and defeat the Humongonauts, the rift in the gang is deep and the question by the end of the episode soon becomes can Mystery Inc. ever be healed again?

removed.title: What the Hex Is Going On?
removed.description: When the gang visits the Weatherby estate, they must investigate a mysterious voice and a ghost who demands the family return its fortune to a neighboring clan.

removed.title: The Secret of the Ghost Rig
removed.description: A mysterious ghost trucker is terrorizing Crystal Cove. Add to that all the doorknobs have begun to disappear from around town, someone has hidden a priceless diamond and Fred's dad, the Mayor, is up for re-election against a guy named Avocados. Scooby and the gang have their hands full. Oh, and did we mention Daphne has been set-up on a blind date with a pinhead named Rung Ladderton, who - wait for it - sells ladders for a living.

removed.title: Haunted House Hang-Up
removed.description: The gang investigates a haunted southern mansion when the Mystery Machine overheats and strands them nearby.

removed.title: The Grasp of the Gnome
removed.description: The Royal Knights Faire has come to Crystal Cove and the whole gang is in attendance. Unfortunately, so is a scary gnome who has begun attacking and paralyzing guests. Specifically, guests who are wearing pirate costumes. The gang decides to help trap the gnome. But when Shaggy, who is dressed as a pirate along with Scooby, is captured by the frightening little beast, it quickly becomes a race against time to find him or Scooby could lose his best buddy forever.

removed.title: The Legend of Alice May
removed.description: There's a new girl at Crystal Cove High named Alice May and she's set her romantic sights on Fred. Only one problem, Alice is dead! That's right, Fred's new girlfriend is a dead girl. Alice is a ghost, famous for snatching up guys like Fred and disappearing with them forever. Now, she wants to take Fred to the prom, which means he's next. Fortunately, Daphne also wants to go to the prom with Fred and she's not going to let Alice beat her to the "punch" bowl (wink-wink). And what about the rest of the gang? Well, they've got problems of their own. See, Velma wants to go the prom with Shaggy but Scooby wants Shaggy to watch a Vincent Van Ghoul marathon with him. You keeping up? Good because this one is going to get nasty and when it's over, Scooby and the gang will never be the same again.

removed.title: In Fear of the Phantom
removed.description: Velma's favorite band, the Hex Girls, is in town and the gang has a front row seat. Unfortunately, so does an evil specter named The Phantom, who wants the Hex Girls out of the music business permanently! Solution? Send Daphne undercover as Crush, the newest member of the band. But when she's nabbed by the Phantom, Fred goes into freakout mode finally realizing he actually has feelings for Daphne. Meanwhile, Scooby and Shaggy are having their own problems due to Shaggy spending too much time with Velma. His solution: replace Shaggy with a puppet.

removed.title: Jeepers It's the Creeper
removed.description: The kids look for a ghostly bank robber, who seems able to walk through walls.

removed.title: The Dragon's Secret
removed.description: After an exchange student named Mai Lee shows up in town to stay with Velma, strange Kung Fu wizards begin attacking the town trying to get her.

removed.title: A Clue for Scooby-Doo
removed.description: Scooby and the gang become mixed up in a mystery when he surfs into what appears to be the ghost of Captain Cutler.

removed.title: When the Cicada Calls
removed.description: Bugs are taking over Crystal Cove and attacking some of its most prominent citizens. With Mystery Inc. back together as a team, they begin to investigate and discover all of the attacks have been on employees of a company called Destroido that makes Shaggy and Scooby's favorite snack food - Granma Moonbeams Nature Slivers. Somebody or something wants the company shut down. But when the gang gets too close to the truth, they become the bug's newest target. Of course, the timing couldn't be worse because this just happens to be the moment Fred has decided to make his move on Daphne and finally ask her out. That ain't gonna happen, though, if there are a bunch of bugs trying to kill them.

removed.title: All Fear the Freak
removed.description: The mystery comes to a close. The Scooby gang finally gets to the bottom of what happened to the original Mystery Incorporated and why they disappeared.

removed.title: Escape from Mystery Manor
removed.description: The gang investigates the disappearance of the original Mystery Inc. gang.

removed.title: Scooby-Doo and a Mummy, Too
removed.description: The gang helps a professor set up an ancient Egypt exhibit but the star of the display keeps vanishing.

removed.title: The Siren's Song
removed.description: Velma is feeling like a fifth wheel. Fred has Daphne and Shaggy has Scooby. Who does she have?

removed.title: Bedlam in the Big Top
removed.description: A ghost clown haunts a small circus, using hypnotism to bend locals to his will.

removed.title: The Song of Mystery
removed.description: A hideous creature named Que Horrifico is turning the children of Crystal Cove in to monsters. The adults in the town are in shock, reacting in the only way they know how, by abandoning their children and running away like cowards. Only Scooby and the gang stay behind to solve the mystery. Going undercover as a family - "Dad" Fred, "Mom" Daphne, "Grandma" Velma, "Son" Shaggy and "Baby" Scooby - the gang rents a house in order to capture Que Horrifico. But when their plan backfires and Que Horrifico uses his power over the monster children to cause them to attack the gang, it looks like all is lost. That is until a cartoon character named Broccoli Head comes to their rescue.

removed.title: Mystery Mask Mix-Up
removed.description: When Daphne innocently buys a mask that once belonged to an ancient warlord, the gang finds itself pursued by zombies and ghosts.

removed.title: Where Walks Aphrodite
removed.description: Love has come to Crystal Cove. Love in the form of an evil woman by the name of Aphrodite.

removed.title: Pawn of Shadows
removed.description: The Scooby gang is getting close to finally unraveling what happened to the original Mystery Incorporated kids.

removed.title: Mine Your Own Business
removed.description: The gang explores a mining town and investigate a phantom miner, who's driving the business away from a nearby dude ranch.

removed.title: Night Fright
removed.description: Scooby and Shaggy win a dinner date with their hero, Vincent Van Ghoul.

removed.title: Attack of the Headless Horror
removed.description: Fred's favorite adventurer, Rick Spartan, has come to town to take over the school's biology class.

removed.title: Beware the Beast from Below
removed.description: Crystal Cove may be the most haunted town in the world but that doesn't stop Scooby and the gang from trying to prove that most of its most famous tourist attractions were fakes, much to the anger and dwindling profits of their parents. But when a radioactive barrel is accidentally opened releasing a hideous sewer beast that cocoons its victims in frozen yogurt, their mystery-solving skills are put to the test. After all, what could a sewer beast, a delicious edible dessert, underground caves and shrimping boats made of balloons possibly have in common? I'll give you a little hint - the local bank.

removed.title: Decoy for a Dognapper
removed.description: Scooby impersonates a prize-winning Great Dane to catch whoever is stealing show dogs.

removed.title: The Secret Serum
removed.description: There's a vampire loose in the town terrorizing the residents and stealing an odd assortment of loot. When the gang does some sniffing around, they discover an unlikely suspect - Daphne's mother. Things are already strained within Mystery Inc. and with this latest blow, the gang is truly torn in half. Girls on one side, boys on the other. Although they solve the mystery in the end, the rift in Mystery Inc. is now complete. They are a team no more.

removed.title: The Backstage Rage
removed.description: A sinister puppet master manipulates the gang's investigation of a case of counterfeit.

removed.title: The Creeping Creatures
removed.description: A long time ago, there was a town called Gatorburg, where gators flowed wild and free and people got rich. Now, it's a ghost town. Gators are all dried up. But when Scooby and the gang receive an imitation Gatorburg purse, they decide to see for themselves if the gators really are gone. Forced to stay overnight when someone steals the engine to the Mystery Machine, they soon discover that gators have indeed returned - only these have comb-overs, walk on two legs and don't like visitors.

removed.title: A Tiki Scare Is No Fair
removed.description: A Hawaiian vacation turns into another investigation when Scooby and Shaggy are threatened by a witch doctor.

removed.title: Foul Play in Funland
removed.description: The gang investigates a haunted seaside amusement park.

removed.title: Revenge of the Man Crab
removed.description: While hosting a volleyball tournament for Trickell's Triquid diet moisture, a smooth drinking beverage just like water except not so fatty, Crystal Cove beach finds itself attacked by a hideous man crab, who has taken a liking to the tournament's female players. Desperate to stop this beast before it scares away all the tourists, the gang investigates convinced it is a disgruntled local named Skipper Shelton, famous for his delicious clam filled waffle cones, his missing nose and his hatred for Crystal Cove bureaucrats. But when Daphne is captured by the Man Crab, Scooby and the gang have to put the mystery solving into overdrive or risk losing not only Daphne but the sanity of their leader Fred, who is not taking the abduction well.

removed.title: A Night of Fright Is No Delight
removed.description: Scooby must spend the night in a haunted house in order to receive an inheritance.

removed.title: What a Night for a Knight
removed.description: Scooby-Doo and Shaggy stumble across a lone suit of black armor and embark on a quest to find the artifact's missing owner.

removed.title: That's Snow Ghost
removed.description: A ski trip turns spooky for the gang when they run into the ghostly Yeti Beast and a Tibetan hermit, who says he is responsible for summoning the monster.

removed.title: Howl of the Fright Hound
removed.description: After a horrible, mechanized beast begins attacking the town, all fingers begin pointing at Scooby. Before the gang can clear his name, the Sheriff has Scooby hauled away to the Crystal Cove Hospital for Criminally Insane Animals. Now, it's up to the gang to clear Scooby's good name. But standing in their way is a new enemy they hadn't counted on: a diabolical parrot named Professor Pericles, who knows more about Mystery Inc. than he should. Add to this the growing friction between Shaggy, Velma and Scooby, and you have a recipe for disaster.

removed.title: A Gaggle of Galloping Ghosts
removed.description: The gang visits Franken Castle, which seems to be crowded with famous inhabitants Dracula, the Monster and Wolf Man.

removed.title: Mystery Solvers Club State Finals
removed.description: The Mystery Inc. gang has been invited to compete in the annual Teen Mystery Solver's Convention.

removed.title: A Haunting in Crystal Cove
removed.description: Mayor Jones is under attack by a poltergeist in his own home and the only ones who can help him are the Scooby gang.

removed.title: Hassle in the Castle
removed.description: The sleuths shipwreck on a deserted island and explore a haunted castle.

removed.title: Menace of the Manticore
removed.description: After the Mayor purchases a haunted temple off the internet, Crystal Cove's only theme park, Creepy Spooky Terror Land, is besieged by a Manticore.

removed.title: The Wild Brood
removed.description: A rowdy Orc Biker Gang has decided to roll through Crystal Cove and no one is very happy about it.

removed.title: Scooby's Night with a Frozen Fright
removed.description: Shaggy and Scooby hook a frozen caveman and present the chilly artifact to Oceanland. But the creature is mysteriously thawed out and goes on a rampage.

removed.title: Dead Justice
removed.description: There's a new lawman in town and his name is Dead Justice, an undead cowboy sheriff who used to patrol the streets of Crystal Cove.

removed.title: Who's Afraid of the Big Bad Werewolf
removed.description: The gang goes camping and stumbles across a lonely graveyard and an empty tomb, whose missing inhabitant was suspected of being a werewolf.

removed.title: The Shrieking Madness
removed.description: With Mystery Inc. broken up, the gang decides to check out life after high school and spend a weekend at Darrow College. But things don't go as planned when a creature called Char Gar Gothakon begins terrorizing the campus. Turns out, this beast is a fictional character come to life. A creation of the author H.P. Hatecraft, who is a professor at the school. Although one of the other professors, Harlan Ellison, claims Hatecraft is a fraud, the creature is definitely real. And when it attacks and carries off Hatecraft to his doom, the gang realizes it has to come together once again to solve this mystery and save Hatecraft's life.

removed.title: Go Away Ghost Ship
removed.description: The gang sets out to solve the mystery of a ghostly pirate seemingly bent on avenging his capture by a shipping magnate's ancestor.

removed.title: Which Witch Is Which?
removed.description: A zombie walks in front of the Mystery Machine as the gang heads into the bayou for a fishing trip, leading to a real witch hunt.

removed.title: Spooky Space Kook
removed.description: The gang stumbles across a UFO's landing site when the Mystery Machine runs out of gas on a deserted road.

removed.title: Don't Fool with a Phantom
removed.description: A phantom interrupts Shaggy and Scooby's performance on a TV dance show.

removed.title: Nowhere to Hyde
removed.description: The gang follows a mysterious figure through a marsh to the house of a latter-day Dr. Jekyll, whose alter ego is apparently a jewel thief.
